      <hedline>
        <hl1>Making It in This New Economy</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Alvin Patrick letter disputes September 25 Op-Ed article by Ann L Berrios describing her financial straits in booming economy</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''No Wealth of Opportunity,'' by Ann L. Berrios (Op-Ed, Sept. 25):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''No Wealth of Opportunity,'' by Ann L. Berrios (Op-Ed, Sept. 25):</p>
        <p>It seems to me that Ms. Berrios doesn't understand how the American economy functions. Opportunity is everywhere, but one has to take advantage of favorable circumstances.</p>
        <p>For instance, Ms. Berrios could have gotten an M.B.A. or a law degree at night instead of a master's in liberal studies. Her husband, who she mentioned is a science professor, could take advantage of the boom in the technology sector. A roaring economy does not guarantee wealth to a science professor and a clerical worker -- or anyone, for that matter.  ALVIN PATRICK  New York, Sept. 25, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a TV producer.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
